               IMPORTANT NOTICE from the District of Massachusetts
                    PACER Administrator, Edis Feldhouse :

     Click to Log-In to the District of Massachusetts WebPacer

   The U.S. District Court for the District of Massachusetts is currently
   providing Federal Court case information on the Internet. Traditional
   dial-up PACER is still available if you experience trouble accessing
   this site. Whether you access PACER on the Internet or use the dial-up
   service, you will be required to use a login and password issued by the
   PACER Service Center. If you do not already have a PACER account, you
   may call (800) 676-6856 or (210) 301-6440 to obtain a registration form
   or you can register on-line by visiting the Pacer Service Center
   web-site. It takes about a week to receive a login and password from
   the PACER Service Center.

   There is a $.07 per page charge for downloading case information on
   this system.

   The Judiciary is always open to suggestions from our public access
   users. If you have comments or questions, contact the PACER Service
   Center by phone at (800) 676-6856 or (210) 301-6440, or send email to
   pacer@psc.uscourts.gov. Please include the name of the specific court
   you are referring to in your email when writing to the PACER Service
   Center.
